<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 01 at 3:27PM CDT  by NWS Mobile</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Perry
and eastern Stone Counties through 415 PM CDT...
At 327 PM CDT, National Weather Service doppler radar indicated a
strong thunderstorm near Perkinston, or 6 miles southeast of Wiggins,
moving northeast at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Wiggins and Perkinston.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
